{"type":"message","id":"c179dcf1","parentId":"d838893e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:47:05.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the current implementation. Let me analyze:\n\n**Current features (10):**\n1. rsi\n2. log_vr\n3. lb (连板数)\n4. trend_up\n5. above_ma20\n6. jb_prob\n7. rsi_high\n8. rsi_low\n9. lb_high\n10. lb_mid\n\n**Current model performance:**\n- AUC-ROC: 0.6097\n- Accuracy: 63.9%\n- Precision: 89.3%\n- Recall: 66.0%\n\n**New features to add:**\nA. 竞价特征 (auction): auction_chng, auction_bid, auction_volume_ratio\n\n\nB. 板块特征 (sector): sector_hot_count, sector_signal\nC. 市场情绪 (market): market_temperature, zbgc_rate, rise_fall_ratio\nD. 历史特征 (historical): stock_hist_win_rate, stock_hist_seal_rate, stock_zt_count\nE. 筹码特征 (chips): turnover_rate, volume_change\nF. 时间特征 (time): is_monday, close_plate_time\n\nI need to build an enhanced training script that incorporates these new features with multi-threaded processing for efficiency.\n\nMy approach will be to first explore the database schema to understand what data's available, then write the enhanced training script, execute it, and generate a report. The model will save as xgb_model_v2.pkl with corresponding metadata in model_metadata_v2.json.\n\nLet me start by examining the database structure.","thinkingSignature":"668c0791a9928b0f73ae64f3882c6d2c4f6f5a08227cbd8702c42b8521021abe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_612sxvk6la2w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace && python3 -c \"\nimport sqlite3\nconn = sqlite3.connect('data/astock/model/astock.db')\ncur = conn.cursor()\n\n# 列出所有表\ncur.execute(\\\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type='table'\\\")\ntables = cur.fetchall()\nprint('Tables:', [t[0] for t in tables])\n\n# 查看predictions表结构\ncur.execute('PRAGMA table_info(predictions)')\ncols = cur.fetchall()\nprint('\\npredictions columns:')\nfor c in cols:\n    print(f'  {c[1]} {c[2]}')\n\n# 查看前3条数据\ncur.execute('SELECT * FROM predictions LIMIT 3')\nrows = cur.fetchall()\nprint('\\nSample data:')\nfor row in rows:\n    print(row)\n\"\n","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10866,"output":535,"cacheRead":25966,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37367,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774284412545}}
